## Adaptive Pre-Launch Tuner

### `adaptive.AdaptivePrelaunchTuner`

Runs immediately before launch on a **fresh GameConfig** from the recommender or saved store.  
Adjusts config fields based on **current** device state — not hardware maximums.

```kotlin
fun tune(config: GameConfig, context: Context): GameConfig {
    val thermal  = powerManager.getThermalHeadroom(5).coerceIn(0f, 1f)
    val availMb  = activityManager.getMemoryInfo().availMem / (1024 * 1024)

    val fpsLimit = when {
        thermal < 0.20f -> minOf(config.fpsLimit.ifUncapped(60), 30)  // device already hot
        thermal < 0.40f -> minOf(config.fpsLimit.ifUncapped(60), 45)  // warming up
        else            -> config.fpsLimit
    }
    val dxvkBudget = when {
        availMb < 1_800 -> 1_024   // critically low — minimal DXVK footprint
        availMb < 3_000 -> 1_536   // low — conservative budget
        else            -> config.dxvkDeviceLocalMemoryMiB
    }
    val resScale = when {
        availMb < 1_800 -> 0.65f.coerceAtMost(config.resolutionScale)
        availMb < 2_500 -> 0.75f.coerceAtMost(config.resolutionScale)
        else            -> config.resolutionScale
    }
    return config.copy(fpsLimit = fpsLimit, dxvkDeviceLocalMemoryMiB = dxvkBudget, resolutionScale = resScale)
}
```

**Do NOT tune DXVK_ASYNC, ESYNC, FSYNC, or CPU affinity** — those are always-on and have no downside.

