## Dynamic Memory Management

### Memory pressure thresholds

| Available RAM | Action |
|---|---|
| > 4 GB | Full DXVK budget (40% of total RAM), native resolution |
| 2.5–4 GB | DXVK budget = 1.8 GB, resolution unchanged |
| 1.8–2.5 GB | DXVK budget = 1.2 GB, resolution −0.10x |
| < 1.8 GB | DXVK budget = 1 GB, resolution −0.25x, disable VKD3D if DX11 possible |

### Shader cache eviction

At game launch, check total size of all shader caches under `GamePaths.getDxvkCacheDir()`.  
If total > 2 GB, evict caches for games not launched in 30+ days (sorted by last access time).  
Log eviction with `Timber.tag("ShaderCache")` so the user can see it in diagnostics.

### Wine memory settings

Inside the container launch script, always set these before Wine starts — they prevent Wine from fragmenting the heap and reduce OOM risk:

```bash
export WINEDEBUG=-all                     # no logging overhead
export STAGING_SHARED_MEMORY=1            # use shared memory for IPC (less duplication)
export WINE_LARGE_ADDRESS_AWARE=1         # allow 32-bit games to access > 2 GB
ulimit -n 1048576                         # ESYNC requirement — must not be removed
```

